New Records: Starter Spencer Strider reached a milestone with his nine strikeouts, now having 424 strikeouts in his first 50 career starts, the most since 1893.
Key Match Events: The Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title by defeating the Philadelphia Phillies 4-1.
Spencer Strider secured his major league-leading 17th win.
Austin Riley hit a two-run homer.
Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game.
Austin Riley homered in the first inning and hit a sacrifice fly in the third.
Kevin Pillar doubled in the fourth inning to score Marcell Ozuna.
Post-Match Reflections: Braves manager Brian Snitker said, 'We’ve checked one box.'

Phillies slugger Kyle Schwarber commented, 'Did we want it to be on our field? No. But they’re going to have to do it somewhere. The focus is on us, still. We’re going to keep pushing until the very end.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves became the first team to clinch a playoff berth with a 5-2 win over the Pittsburgh Pirates on September 10.
The Braves own the best record in baseball.
This is the Braves' sixth straight division title and their 18th as a franchise.
The Braves clinched in 146 games, their second-quickest clinch in the divisional era.
The division title was the Braves’ record 26th, two more than the Los Angeles Dodgers and New York Yankees.
The Braves have gone nearly wire-to-wire in the 2023 season, spending only one day in 2nd place in early April.
The Braves took special satisfaction in clinching on the same Citizens Bank Park field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series.
